WHAT IS
First-class value (, first-class object, or first-class functions) ?
-> values that can be passed to functions as argument or retunred by those functions.
*function is one of First-class value in JS*


WHAT IS 
Higher Order Functions?
->functions that take other functions as argument. 

the functions we pass to higher order functions are called "callback functions" or "callback".
ex)arr.forEach(a => console.log(a)) .. 
forEach: higher order function
function (a) {return console.log(a)}: callback

